	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 5th 4:10 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.99]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi, I am a lvl 50 paladin & my guild just had a mass exodus of lvl 50+ players. We are left with just one Lvl 49+ cleric. <br>I have an other account with a lvl 24 cleric, that is basically twinked, my son's a/c, that he quit playing. (The high lvl guildees started to twink this guy to get him up to res capability)<br>I just started to play this guy, thinking that if I can get him Power levelled, he will contribute to the guild raiding ability. <br>I was surprised to note that in LOIO & i tackle a blue con goblin Aggressor, I may be able to out melee this critter, I did not, I just rooted , nuked a few times, feared when root quit, then just pounded it into submission. I believe I could have melee'd him to death as well.<br>My cleric needs wis gear bad, he has sebilite scale bp & legs & other stuff like a smoldering brand that has a small proc (9/22 i think)& sports a velium round shield. Wis is only 135 or so, so i need more wis stuff like jewelry & better shield. He's a gnome cleric btw. <br>I had some fun kicking that Goblins butt, <br>What would be a good solo strategy for Goblin Aggressors & say Sarnack enforcers. root/nuke/root/nuke?<br>I think holy might/ root/ nuke/fear then Club it to death while chasing. <br>Or should i just stand in there swinging. I think I have like 600+hp + 500 ac(or the other way around).<br><br>I could get some guild members to come & really PL me , but i need to learn how to play the cleric first. <br>Group healing & buffing, I am sure i can do np, I need to determine the effectiveness of some of the spells we cast.<br>I am familiar with a lot of the spells, because my main is lvl 50 pally. My Pally has done a lot of grouping with clerics , so i am familiar with the role in a group, or what i expect a good cleric to do in a group. The challenge for me, is to learn how to fight with a cleric, to get fast exp. <br>I think at lvl 25 I will head to HK because i know that the grp exp rocks in there. But i need a crash course in the fighting capability of a cleric.<br>Thanks for your advice!<br>Torsk Holynite, Ad Gloriam<br>(Playing his lvl 24 Cleric)<br>Lanys T'Vyl<br>ps. I have seen some 50+ clerics Solo in places where my paladin ( when he was lvl 45) would not dream of surrviving in. ie MM/Unrest basenment. So I know that the 50+ Cleric is an awsome wonder, when played right!<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
