<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10025442873371></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10025442873371><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10025442873371>RE: Help a cousin!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=10025442873371#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 8th 8:31 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Cleric root is not a great root, even at high levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;It can and generally does get broken by DD, particularly by wrath and retrib etc.  hehe I get a nice warm feeling when I can cast 2 to 3 times without it breaking.  Best bet is nuke, then root.  Sit and med for a mana increase and the spell icons lighting back up, then nuke and root again, being prepared to get pounded when the root is resisted/your spell fizzles.<br><br>Clerics do not good soloers make.  We can, that is true, but we are not good at it.  Read a few cleric guides, particularly on healing/buffing, then get a few groups and try yourself out. But remember your MAJOR role in a group is to keep people alive, not to kill mobs.  If you prefer soloing, clerics are not your best bet by a long shot.<br><br>HighHold Keep is a great place to learn clericking, particularly if you can get into the lookout group at 19 or 20.  Don't try to heal for a pit group (warriors/raiders) until at least L24 when you get greater healing (288-300hps a cast), as up till then you will only be healing for 100 a cast, and gob warriors and raiders can do far more damage than you could hope to keep up with.  (I spent most of my time from L20 to L34 in the Keep basement.)<br><br>Or, if you prefer, team up with a L20ish tank and go kill Osargen in the Keep for huge xps.  He is a permanent L22 6 minute spawn and will stay blue for you till L31.<br><br>Yaninya Demure<br>Vicar, The Rathe<br>Child of the New Sun<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
